body: Hello - are your results correct though (despite the warnings) ?

Looks like a converter issue with Slice nodes. The 3 Slice nodes are claiming that the output shape matches the input shape. e.g. Slice_10, Slice_15 and Slice_20 all have input and output of shape {B, T} which is incorrect given the parameters to the Slice op. 

The output shape should be {B, 1} for Slice_10 and {B, T-1} for the other two. 

A symbolic name is assumed to only ever have one value. We re-use buffers where possible if the shape matches, and because of the incorrectly declared output shapes we are re-using a buffer. The warning happens when we see the actual shapes of the buffers don't match. As the re-use requires a smaller buffer we allow it, but it's just luck that the re-use requires a smaller buffer. 

How was the model exported? From pytorch?
Yes, it was exported from PyTorch. It traces a LogFilterBank frontend that does preemphasis and thus uses T-1 tensor as intermediate value. It seems to still work correctly, yes.
Sure, I can take a look. Thanks for your investigation.

issue.title: Fix Slice op's shape inference logic

repository.name: onnx
repository.description: Open standard for machine learning interoperability

issue.body:
Slice shape inference has logic to copy over `dim_value` and `dim_param` from the input to the output prior to processing each dimension specified by the `axes` input. In case, we cannot proceed with processing a particular dimension, any copied over `dim_param` (if any in the copy step) must be cleared to leave it truly "empty".

Resolve https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/2756

CC: @skottmckay

body: Looks like there are some ONNX build issues meaning it could take awhile to get the fix PR merged and consume it in ONNXRuntime. I ll close this issue when the fix PR is merged in ONNX and consumed here.

issue.title: Export to ONNX of nop-squeeze errors out in ONNXRT

labels.name: triaged
labels.description: This issue has been looked at a team member, and triaged and prioritized into an appropriate module

repository.name: pytorch
repository.description: Tensors and Dynamic neural networks in Python with strong GPU acceleration

issue.body:
Squeeze of dimension 1 is a no-op, since it's not squeezable. However when exported to ONNX it produces an ONNXRT error. Maybe it's a problem in nop `squeeze(1)` export, maybe in ONNXRT.

```python
import torch
import onnxruntime

bug = True

class Preemphasis(torch.nn.Module):
    def forward(self, signal):
        if bug:
            signal = signal.squeeze(1)
        signal = torch.cat([signal[..., :1], signal[..., 1:] - 0.97 * signal[..., :-1]], dim = -1)
        return signal

frontend = Preemphasis()
input = torch.rand(16, 8000)
torch.onnx.export(frontend, (input,), 'model.onnx', opset_version = 10, export_params = True, do_constant_folding = True, input_names = ['signal'], output_names = ['output'], dynamic_axes = dict(signal = {0 : 'B', 1 : 'T'}, output = {0 : 'B', 1: 'T'}))
(output_, ) = onnxrt_session.run(None, dict(signal = input.cpu().numpy()))

output = frontend(input)
assert torch.allclose(output.cpu(), torch.from_numpy(output_), rtol = 1e-02, atol = 1e-03)
```

produces
```

```
